<subSubSection id="785157595AFF7D77E6334D7C71048193" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="35039636D268E7F2F6432EC03EA9BB84" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF396AD7B8DAF3836B902F162B43D8A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="4D1A3455870A26D84C8331172FA9C61A" authorityName="M. Tang, G. J. Yan &amp; W. P. Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster quanzhouensis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quanzhouensis">
<emphasis id="1CDABD9D240E13A7043FC8536FEE6486" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Aster quanzhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F4028ADA374A7DDC3424B02A5B496FFB" genus="A." lsidName="A. tonglingensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="tonglingensis">
<emphasis id="BC6C8F946C98CA824FA31642E83EE5A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A. tonglingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its stems only 21-30 (60) cm (vs. 70-100 cm) long, narrowly lanceolate (vs. lanceolate) rosulate leaves, purplish-red (vs. green) apices of the phyllaries, 9-20 (40) (vs. more than 30) capitula, 7-11 (vs. ca. 15) ray florets, 11-14 
<normalizedToken id="E0D581AAF33339F43BE6B6C8CC645899" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 2 mm (vs. 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="436800A27429BEB81361C8173FFC771B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 2 mm) lamina, two-or three-ribbed (vs. 4-ribbed) achenes and flowering period (Sep to early Dec vs. Jul) (Figs 
<figureCitation id="F5912537E372144BBABA5ECBB2EF7F88" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Images of living plants of Aster quanzhouensis A habitat B habit C seedling D steam E rosulate leaves F top view of the capitulum G a disk floret (left) and a ray floret (right) H style branches of a disk floret I receptacle J fruits K dorsal view of a capitulum L phyllaries (from outer to inner, left to right)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.195.82411.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/681668" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A97B2315B2966B7ADA55D4DB0DC3D2D5" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Holotype of Aster quanzhouensis M. Tang, G. J. Yan &amp; W. P. Li." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.195.82411.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/681669" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">3</figureCitation>
, Table 
<tableCitation id="9E46BC85B2DF31D598CED00D71E9EB24" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of Aster quanzhouensis and A. tonglingensis. The data of the latter species were taken from Zhang et al. (2019)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/668C20FBB39145E7FAAD7D06E202CDCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" tableUuid="668C20FBB39145E7FAAD7D06E202CDCE">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="668C20FBB39145E7FAAD7D06E202CDCE" ID-Table-UUID="668C20FBB39145E7FAAD7D06E202CDCE" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/668C20FBB39145E7FAAD7D06E202CDCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
<paragraph id="5B13CEA5E57CA1C66B0733E07324621E" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="4F5CAAD38B98A598823FC5774E4FBF9F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Table 1.</emphasis>
Comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="937B9D21C542CF8E8F98A9778656D3DB" authorityName="M. Tang, G. J. Yan &amp; W. P. Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster quanzhouensis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quanzhouensis">
<emphasis id="DBDD1698B32C6045AB62AC70EB99ABD2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Aster quanzhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="487A8751283E6BD9A4E66A806B5E7C1D" genus="A." lsidName="A. tonglingensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="tonglingensis">
<emphasis id="50811B11E75FA3ACD1F3A9FD2346447D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A. tonglingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The data of the latter species were taken from 
<bibRefCitation id="AE7612468BCAD3B539CAC7F85AAF9F40" DOI="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.6288" author="Zhang, GJ" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" refId="B27" refString="Zhang, GJ, Hu, HH, Gao, TG, Gilbert, MG, Jin, XF, 2019. Convergent origin of the narrowly lanceolate leaf in the genus Aster-with special reference to an unexpected discovery of a new Aster species from East China. PeerJ 7: e6288. https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.6288" title="Convergent origin of the narrowly lanceolate leaf in the genus Aster-with special reference to an unexpected discovery of a new Aster species from East China. PeerJ 7: e 6288." url="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.6288" year="2019">Zhang et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
